  I agree.  I'm not one to go cemetari=
es.  And I did tell my contacts what I would be doing.  I get images of it =
being almost like an amusement park for them.  Where they can go to have so=
me fun with the physical. 

  But the energy here was amazing! It didn't fe=
el bad at all. The only part of the cemetary that gave me bad vibes was thi=
s old tree in the back. My husband said that by the way it looks it could h=
ave been a hanging tree.  They hung the criminals there and buried them in =
the woods.  So that was more of a psychic imprint from the past.

  Jody

    HI Frank,
    I don't think they=
 do naturally hang around graveyards.  I think they are there when we recor=
d or just let them know of our presence.  I know that Braden and friends co=
me to talk just about wherever we are, and that includes the graveyard.  Ba=
yview Cemetery is considered one of the most haunted in Washington state an=
d is just down the road from me and Mary Jo.  Once we went into the mausole=
um there, where it was pretty darn scary.  Neither of us got an EVP or an a=
nomalous photo there, despite the strange vibes.  Vicki

    Sumption Frank=

nceptions!
       Frank

      Any way.  There was this one Gra=
ve that we believed was Elizabeths.  We went over there 3 times and could s=
mell lilacs after awhile.  It wasn't immediate, it just slowly came upon us=
. There was nothing around us to create that odor (not even in the woods), =
so I'm guessing they were sending it to us. When I say "what are these" I w=
as picking up some of those purple flowers that grow from clover.  They did=
 not produce the scent we were smelling!! It was incredible.  I have experi=
enced this before and to me, it means close to the same thing as roses.  A =
welcoming, of love and peace.
